DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl", "PGbasicmacros.pl", "PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl");

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(&beginproblem);

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

# output the text of the problem

$a = random(2,20,1);
$b = random(2,20,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the vertex of the parabola \( y= (x-$a)^2 + $b \) and determine whether it
is a minimum or maximum .

The vertex is the point ( \{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\} ) 
and it is a (MIN or MAX) \{ans_rule(10)\}
        
EOT

$ans1 = $a;
$ans2 = $b;
$ans3 = "MIN";

&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans1));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans2));
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans3));


